    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Slice your<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into discs and add them to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 15-20 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/potato-topped-peri-peri-basa-pie/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice your<strong> red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/potato-topped-peri-peri-basa-pie/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 15g <span class=\"text-purple\">[25g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[30g] </span><strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> red wine vinegar </strong>and <strong>dried</strong> <strong>oregano</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>peri-peri paste</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/potato-topped-peri-peri-basa-pie/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>peri-peri paste </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong>,<strong> </strong>mix everything together and cook for 2-3 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 200ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [340ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong>, 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> and your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 3-4 min or until slightly thickened</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/potato-topped-peri-peri-basa-pie/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the sauce is thickening, chop your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped basa </strong>to the<strong> </strong>sauce and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>peri-peri</strong> <strong>basa pie filling</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/potato-topped-peri-peri-basa-pie/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>peri-peri basa pie filling</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> and top with the <strong>potato discs </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> potato-topped peri-peri basa pie</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 15-20 min or until the fish is cooked through and the pie is bubbling and golden</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/potato-topped-peri-peri-basa-pie/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>shredded kale </strong>then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>shredded kale</strong> with a splash of <strong>cold water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until tender with a bite</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/potato-topped-peri-peri-basa-pie/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>potato-topped peri-peri basa pie </strong>with the<strong> shredded kale </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
